<subSubSection id="3250BCA6E3F42FC3342BA9D1349E4BB8" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="description">
<paragraph id="D861059D895B3DF9ACA63B69227970CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BCAA51A004E4DDC1CD04918C72FD7230" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="1A70A21647815B305A6B69D0DFDD2903" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Female (n = 3).</emphasis>
Body length 7.7-7.9 mm, polished, coriaceous, covered with silver setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D97462501840F2203BE1B1EFB20C1079" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="94D7B5F6B3E1CFC2CD74FE27FCF41B54" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Head</emphasis>
0.47-0.52 
<normalizedToken id="1805442C4653456FE960C702DB4D56CF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. Clypeus 1.78-2.0 
<normalizedToken id="8F34CDDD50635A1FD8A3126B960AE3B9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as high, convex basally in lateral view. Face 2.6-2.9 
<normalizedToken id="65FAE06F9128B865A895B676D94FAAA4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as high, densely punctate, convex medially in lateral view, separated from clypeus by shallow clypeal sulcus. Inner orbits strongly divergent downward (Figs 
<figureCitation id="787A98CF178F207E0BAF543F7D7A7588" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Woldstedtius takagii (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female) - A. Habitus; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667927" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="42C6DFB9E2D62F2CD874AC516B91C23C" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Japanese Woldstedtius A, G. W. f. flavolineatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); B, I. W. kuroashii (Uchida, 1957); C, D, K. W. takagii (Uchida, 1957); E. W. alpicola sp. nov.; F. W. biguttatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); H. W. karafutensis (Uchida, 1957); J. W. punctatus sp. nov. (E, J. holotype; B, I. paratype) - A, B. head, lateral view; C. head, frontal view; D. propodeum, lateral view; E-K. T I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667929" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">9C</figureCitation>
). Length of malar space 1.0-1.1 
<normalizedToken id="01D2C7279AA554290183136FE8AF2E45" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as basal mandibular width. POL 2.0-2.15 
<normalizedToken id="0D283CACAFE6AA4CB98CB6E3685B2484" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OD. OOL 1.05-1.25 
<normalizedToken id="3DAD4A31BB0D77FB1903F86BB1225168" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OD. POL 1.8-1.9 
<normalizedToken id="1DF044406F1F415CEC4C6AB05208BCD8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OOL. Antenna with 25-26 flagellomeres. FL I 1.2-1.33 
<normalizedToken id="BCF98A6DD7EF5D2D7799A6F99C438ECF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as FL II. MP IV 1.25-1.4 
<normalizedToken id="03E2634BD9A1A8F8D20CB1E109D1F001" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as MP V.
</paragraph>
<caption id="102862150D3D387181CA7696C0856FE4" doi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667927" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
<paragraph id="5A14F59F01F50CBC09459517C2835699" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="F49D95EE13869D08D7A93593AA2627AC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Figure 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="954858DC1E2B67670385DD812C1660EA" baseAuthorityName="Uchida" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Woldstedtius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Woldstedtius takagii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takagii">
<emphasis id="C9C193D3CB11E2D21DCEADC743BB5BE5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Woldstedtius takagii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Uchida, 1957) (
<emphasis id="261539ABA56D6B3C8BE5164066D64434" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">A-D.</emphasis>
female) - 
<emphasis id="CBDBB5D15FE39F19B19C2D56DC2B100D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">A.</emphasis>
Habitus; 
<emphasis id="C31BBC4A232CD925A9DCB0F8BABAF8CB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">B.</emphasis>
Head, frontal view; 
<emphasis id="AD3A06336985E57595FDAA2174B4678E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">C.</emphasis>
Mesonotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="C19D1FDE9B12BA988A558D57011299A1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">D.</emphasis>
Propodeum, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="F6AA18357A13A804EFC49003F03AF766" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="EFBBE56AA3FC563D28CD769D52A3D067" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="E17A2BF3366AFBFA094525A9271F91DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Lateral aspect of pronotum strigose anteriorly. Mesoscutum finely and densely punctate (separated by ca. 0.8-1.0 
<normalizedToken id="B6A94A6A0892FFF5872FB7F56A1A66E9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their diameter) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="935D0108BE5B91D5B8F9AFE751B01746" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Woldstedtius takagii (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female) - A. Habitus; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667927" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7C</figureCitation>
). Scutellum finely and densely punctate (separated by ca. 0.8-1.0 
<normalizedToken id="D2A84A43D1B20CD69ECB295703394BCC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their diameter) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="023E76055710BC368AE7D4408F1B4714" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Woldstedtius takagii (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female) - A. Habitus; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667927" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7C</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron coarsely and densely punctate except for the areas on and below speculum. Sternaulus weakly impressed. Propodeum weakly protruded basal 0.2 in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ED4F3678458B998B2BE7DE4674A1C75F" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Japanese Woldstedtius A, G. W. f. flavolineatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); B, I. W. kuroashii (Uchida, 1957); C, D, K. W. takagii (Uchida, 1957); E. W. alpicola sp. nov.; F. W. biguttatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); H. W. karafutensis (Uchida, 1957); J. W. punctatus sp. nov. (E, J. holotype; B, I. paratype) - A, B. head, lateral view; C. head, frontal view; D. propodeum, lateral view; E-K. T I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667929" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">9D</figureCitation>
), rugulose (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C3D646B56C88A1084CD1A4524E7F3928" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Woldstedtius takagii (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female) - A. Habitus; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667927" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7D</figureCitation>
), without carinae except for pleural carina. Fore wing length 6.5-7.4 mm. Nervellus intercepted below middle. Hind femur 4.2-4.3 
<normalizedToken id="12858848229D14FA54804BBC41DC1833" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum depth in lateral view. Hind tibia 7.5 
<normalizedToken id="DC7CFD8D9FF3E9CCD9B8324A24EE88CF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum depth in lateral view. Ratio of length of hind first to fifth tarsomeres 1.0: 0.6-0.7: 0.4: 0.2-0.3: 0.3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF77FD38AC63446C9587EEA09B2C12BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="F409A535A158159B3F79EAE6F476E41B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="8318D51839F7C7022F77705172EA8A91" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
T I nearly square in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EEB767DA4ECC7C08C7FABFE4FB379AC2" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Japanese Woldstedtius A, G. W. f. flavolineatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); B, I. W. kuroashii (Uchida, 1957); C, D, K. W. takagii (Uchida, 1957); E. W. alpicola sp. nov.; F. W. biguttatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); H. W. karafutensis (Uchida, 1957); J. W. punctatus sp. nov. (E, J. holotype; B, I. paratype) - A, B. head, lateral view; C. head, frontal view; D. propodeum, lateral view; E-K. T I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667929" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">9K</figureCitation>
), 0.95-1.05 
<normalizedToken id="C54E72B3FFBF435475CAAB324D61C2E5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum width, rugulose laterally. Latero-median carina present basal ca. 0.5 of T I (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3C2B3460BB8F8519F62B1D95706512FB" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Japanese Woldstedtius A, G. W. f. flavolineatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); B, I. W. kuroashii (Uchida, 1957); C, D, K. W. takagii (Uchida, 1957); E. W. alpicola sp. nov.; F. W. biguttatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); H. W. karafutensis (Uchida, 1957); J. W. punctatus sp. nov. (E, J. holotype; B, I. paratype) - A, B. head, lateral view; C. head, frontal view; D. propodeum, lateral view; E-K. T I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667929" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">9K</figureCitation>
). T II 0.65-0.75 
<normalizedToken id="1F3F3A174CFE6538396E1B137DD9F0A4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum width, striate anteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="349B125F795DD1012D4D16BE79273980" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="16D07869E0CE139D1D698AAB6192650D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="7AA5032489DEE02AF347925DA5F74FEE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Coloration</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BBCC81CA3715BBA6D91B34CFDEC98046" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Woldstedtius takagii (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female) - A. Habitus; B. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667927" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">7A-D</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body (excluding wings and legs) black. Face with a large yellow spot medially (this spot sometimes obscured). Palpi, tegula and mesepisternum yellow (mesepisternum sometimes darkened ventrally). Mandible yellow except for apex and base. Lateral aspect of pronotum with a yellow spot posteriorly. Scutellum with a yellow spot apically. Subtegular ridge often tinged with yellow. Wings hyaline. Veins and pterostigma blackish-brown except for yellowish-brown wing base. Legs yellow to brown. Fore and mid trochanters often tinged with black. Coxae, hind trochanter, hind tibia and hind tarsomeres black. Hind trochantellus and femur reddish-brown to blackish-brown. Base of hind tibia tinged with white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7EE3B87AD84F7A1640766D5318AD426A" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="8922E4FBF9120FA3376869E01F2CAC78" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="300336EADD695CDFABCB0F4CE3A72483" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1BBBD887278963A80937C1E1F57FED00" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F464D98A1FE3C06E0F1D28C8F3914D4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Japan (Hokkaido and Honshu).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D72549BDA04B39E515F1232CFA7A0671" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="bionomics">
<paragraph id="1DC215493261B75C3B7B6E1A564CE692" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Bionomics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1863C0E32867F43F17A38A77298E7797" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Host unknown. Adults were collected in broad-leaved forests of mountainous regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D670F8505722D582AC5A4AA44ECEF7FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="00D6FDF39E8B5C063C720F91751606EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15246E559E55CD21968A25615AF4AF05" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="646193009430F3B6F0100FA89043E4DF" genus="W." lsidName="W. kuroashii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="kuroashii">
<emphasis id="063376D6CA9AD0DE2A5DDFEB170AC562" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">W. kuroashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the following combination of character states in females: inner orbits divergent downward (almost parallel in 
<taxonomicName id="5ED81EEF13158E56B3C8B4A2B812A904" genus="W." lsidName="W. kuroashii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="kuroashii">
<emphasis id="4F9329760409C3091FD923D51F3F1685" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">W. kuroashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); propodeum weakly protruded basal 0.2 in lateral view (rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="AFEFC548798CAA9B84870C39D714734B" genus="W." lsidName="W. kuroashii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="kuroashii">
<emphasis id="77E7DB6A2C1F7D18879BFD9C63D7F2D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">W. kuroashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); yellow shoulder marks of mesoscutum absent (present in 
<taxonomicName id="B87B60BBC7C4E1AC49AF65C6023DEC81" genus="W." lsidName="W. kuroashii" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="kuroashii">
<emphasis id="2380645A0557A5F9EFD3C10D9F07EFA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">W. kuroashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
